es.csic.iiia.nsm.norm.generation.cbr

Class CaseSolution

  • java.lang.Object
    • es.csic.iiia.nsm.norm.generation.cbr.CaseSolution

  • public class CaseSolution
extends java.lang.Object
    A case solution is a solution aimed to solve a conflicting situation described in the CaseDescription of a Case. In particular, a case solution describes what actions are prohibited and obligated for some agents in certain views. For instance, a very simple case solution would contain a single View, and an agent with id agentId which is prohibited to perform a single action in that View
    Author:
    "Javier Morales (jmorales@iiia.csic.es)"
    See Also:
    Case, CaseDescription, View
